Date: Wed 12 Jul 2017
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly disease information 2017; 30(30) [edited] http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=24267


Newcastle disease, Portugal
---------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 12 Jul 2017 from Dr Bernardo Fernando, [General Directorate of Food and Veterinary Services, Ministry of Agriculture, Forestry and Rural Development], Lisbon, Portugal

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 7 Jul 2017
Date of confirmation of the event: 7 Jul 2017
Reason for notification: recurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: August 1997
Manifestation of disease: sub-clinical infection
Causal agent: Newcastle disease virus
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1 (01/2017): Mira, Coimbra, DSVR Do Centro [Centro Region Directorate of Food and Veterinary Services]
Date of start of the outbreak: 7 Jul 2017
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: other
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Birds / 71 / 1 / 0 / 71 / 0
Affected populations: 71 racing pigeons. One positive case was detected during routine sampling in closed quarantine premises.

Outbreak statistics: [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Birds / 1.41 / 0 / 0 / 100
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: The positive case (one racing pigeon) was detected in routine sampling in closed quarantine premises. The positive animal was traced back to another racing pigeon holding which is under restriction. Laboratory investigation is ongoing. No commercial farms are present in the 3-km radius of both establishments.

Control measures
Measures applied: screening, traceability, quarantine, official destruction of animal products, official disposal of carcasses, by-products and waste, stamping out, disinfection, vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists), no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
National Farming and Veterinary Investigation Institute (INIAV, I.P.) (national laboratory) / Birds / real-time reverse transcriptase/polymerase chain reaction (RRT-PCR)/ 7 Jul 2017 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map at the source URL above.]

